-- ShangPharma Surges Most in 10 Months on Acquisition Offer
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2012-07-06T17:33:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/shangpharma-surges-most-in-10-months-on-acquisition-offer.html
ShangPharma Corp. (SHP) , a Chinese medical
researcher, surged the most in 10 months in New York after the
company said it may be acquired at a premium to yesterday’s
trading levels.  ShangPharma, based in Shanghai, climbed 18 percent to $8.09
at 1:28 p.m. in New York, the biggest advance since Aug. 12.
Shares had lost 5.4 percent this year through yesterday.  ShangPharma received a non-binding proposal from Xin Hui
and entities affiliated with him, to acquire all of the
company’s outstanding American depositary receipts for $8.50 to
$9.50 per share, according to a statement distributed by
PRNewswire. Shares closed at $6.88 on July 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in  New York  
